									<td valign=top><a name="140"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Poll</strong><br>Who do you think should win Australian Idol? Anthony? or Casey? Have your say in the Community section of our website. <a href="http://community.austnet.org">http://community.austnet.org</a> <br><div class=newscredits>November 17th 12:28pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="115"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>The Do's and Don'ts of the internet</strong><br>A new guide has been added to the support section of this website. Titled "The Do's and Don'ts of the Internet", this guide aims to provide important information and tips that every user should be aware of when either surfing the internet or spending time on AustNet. The guide can be viewed <a href="http://support.austnet.org/dodont.html">HERE</a> (http://support.austnet.org/dodont.html) <br><div class=newscredits>December 11th 6:43am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">xmasblase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="82"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Last Chance to vote</strong><br>Austnet's Ezine is well on it's way to being named. Votes on the name end at 12 noon today AEST (19 May) so if you have not voted yet, please head to <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org">http://community.austnet.org</a> and have your say before the poll closes! <br><div class=newscredits>May 19th 7:44am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="81"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>JAustIRC Chat Applet free to download</strong><br>AustNet users who have long wanted to put a java chat applet on their website to connect to their channel have now had their wish granted, with the release of the JAustIRC java IRC chat applet, coded specifically for AustNet use by <a href="mailto:sophie@austnet.org">Soph</a>.<br />
JAustIRC could not be easier to install and configure, and includes support for the most common AustNet services commands as well as most IRC mode commands.<br />
A zip file with all instructions for installing and configuring the JAustIRC applet is now available for download from <A HREF="http://chat.austnet.org/applet/">http://chat.austnet.org/applet/</a>. Help with installing and configuring the applet can be found online in #austnetwebsite, or on the <A HREF="http://chat.austnet.org/applet">Applet section</a> of this site.<br><div class=newscredits>May 16th 1:03pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="80"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>RSS 2.0 Compatible News Headlines from AustNet</strong><br>Today AustNet revealed its RSS news headline feed. The feed will feature the headlines from the past 10 items of news and is accessible at <a href="file:///C:/Documents and Settings/maintech/My Documents/webs/austnet/headings.xml">http://www.austnet.org/headings.xml</a><br />
This feature was planned from the start and also encouraged by members of AustNet's scripting community. If you wish to know more about RSS 2.0 check out <a href"http://backend.userland.com/rss">http://backend.userland.com/rss</a> The page contains information of what RSS is and much more.<br><div class=newscredits>May 14th 9:02pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="74"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New ircle release</strong><br>On May 2nd, 2003 The ircle developers released ircle release 3.1f1, for Mac users. The Ircle website states that it is likely that this will become the official 3.1 release. It is available for download <a href="file:///C:/Documents and Settings/maintech/My Documents/webs/austnet/support/software/mac.html">Here</a>, or from the Ircle website. <br><div class=newscredits>May 6th 10:49am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="69"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Community Section</strong><br>The community section has had a huge facelift over the previous fortnight as part of stage 2 of the redevelopment of this site. <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org/">http://community.austnet.org</A> brings more interactivity to the site as a whole. Included in this new section is <br />
* a revamped news section, with a form for users to submit news items, <br />
* an expanded channel guide, <br />
* an AustNet quote database with abilities for users to vote for their favourite quotes, and add new quotes;<br />
* a design competition!<br />
and<br />
* AustNet user polls - have your say!<br />
Planned future expansion includes a featured channel archive, Events calendar, and AustNet staff profiles.<br />
Many thanks to the people in #austnetwebsite who have given invaluable feedback and ideas while Karl and Hippychick have been revamping this section.<br><div class=newscredits>May 4th 12:05am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="68"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>mIRC Charity appeal ends</strong><br>The mIRC charity appeal for the Iraq crisis has ended. During the month of April 2003, 100% of the registration fee, for all users who registered their copies of mIRC, was donated to the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies for use in the Iraq appeal. 1301 users registered their copy of mIRC, raising a total of $24,450.00. Click <A HREF="http://www.mirc.co.uk" target="_blank">HERE</a> for more information. <br><div class=newscredits>May 3rd 4:43pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@optusnet.com.au">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="67"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Klient 2.0.15 has been released</strong><br>Klient 2.0.15 is now available to download. This new version includes many fixes and a few visual and behavioral changes. It also includes a 840 page manual about developing DLL Plug-Ins. The Klient installation file is both a full installer and an upgrader. If you already have 2.0 installed, then you shouldn't have any problems upgrading, and all your settings will remain untouched. Changes can be viewed <A HREF="http://www.klient.com/versions.txt" target=_blank>HERE</a><br><div class=newscredits>May 3rd 4:31pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@optusnet.com.au">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="61"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Wanted: Suggestions</strong><br>The AustNet website team is currently collecting suggestions on what users would like to see in the expanded Community section/new AustNet ezine. If you have a suggestion, please email website@austnet.org. <br><div class=newscredits>April 16th 1:17pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="60"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Routing site</strong><br>Austnet today announce a complete revamp of the Austnet.org routing website. The new site includes an in-depth application system, and administration section, with the ability for users to make comments. Aka has been working hard on the site and his work is very much appreciated. http://servers.austnet.org <br><div class=newscredits>April 7th 1:17pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:aka@austnet.org">Aka</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="59"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Subdomains</strong><br>As of today, Austnet users will be able to access the support section of this website via the address http://support.austnet.org, and the community section by http://community.austnet.org. Chat users can simply type http://chat.austnet.org. This should make remembering URLs much simpler for our users, and reflects the commitment AustNet has to growing and supporting it's community. <br><div class=newscredits>April 5th 1:16pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="58"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Austnet Statistics</strong><br>As of today, <http://www.austnet.org/about/">AustNet statistics</a> for the past 24 hours will be available on the site in graph form. User count, channels, server count and IRC Operator count are all graphed, updated hourly. In coming weeks we hope to add weekly graphs and longer term graphs. Karl is responsible for the code behind the graphs and has done a great job. <br><div class=newscredits>April 1st 1:16pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="57"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Software version release for Mac owners</strong><br>Snak version 4.9.2 is now released (previous version 4.9.1), The new version is downloadable from our software section. Snak is also available to download in the following languages: English, German, French, Italian, Spanish, Portuguese, Dutch, Swedish, Norvegian, Danish, Finnish and Catalonian from the Snak website. <br><div class=newscredits>March 11th 1:15pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="56"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Channel of the Week</strong><br>Today sees a new section added to the site - Channel of the week. Each week will see a new channel profiled, and also have a Java Chat module directly into the channel, so you can chat immediately. #funkysexycool is the first channel of the week. <br><div class=newscredits>March 6th 1:14pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="55"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Website</strong><br>What you are looking at is the eagerly awaited redevelopment of the AustNet website. The site is still in an early stage of redevelopment, and you will soon see exciting new content added - including an interactive community section. Thank you to all the people that have contributed with ideas and content, to the site. <br><div class=newscredits>February 23rd 1:14pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
</table>              </p>
